或缺乏运动\,容易导致肌肉僵硬、酸痛和疲劳。本次线上讲座将通过轻松的跟练方式\,带领大家学习传统养生功法八段锦\,帮助舒展筋骨、放松身体\,缓解日常不适\,提升生活的舒适度。 合参加人士 长时间使用电脑或手机的人 久坐工作人士 经常做家务或容易腰背疲劳的人 想学习简单养生运动的中老年人士 如有任何问题\,请联络 文化桥 Trista (LLi@culturelink.ca) 文化桥 Shawna (XZong@culturelink.ca) 西城社区 Wendy(wendy@scaddingcourt.org) 扫瞄以下二维码报名 ﻿ \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Tue		\n		\n			24		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Citizenship Education Circle – Toronto Reference Library	\n\n					\n		\n		March 24 @ 6:00 pm - 8:30 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		Citizenship Education Circle – Toronto Reference Library\n	\n\n\n					\n	\n		Toronto Reference Library	\n	\n		789 Yonge Street\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n					\n\n	\n					\n				Adults	\n\n				\n\n				\n	Are you new to Canada as a Permanent Resident or a Convention Refugee? Every Tuesday at the Toronto Reference Library there will be free weekly sessions to prepare for the […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Thu		\n		\n			26		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Content Creation for Success	\n\n					\n		\n		March 26 @ 4:00 pm - 5:00 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		Content Creation for Success\n	\n\n\n					\n	\n		CultureLink Children & Youth Centre	\n	\n		3535 Dundas Street West\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n									\n\n				\n	Free Workshops For Youth\, Ages 16-30 Learn directly from real influencers! Live Q&A - ask creators anything (growth\, money\, fame) Secrets behind viral videos + follower growth Film + edit […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Thu		\n		\n			26		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Interacthon at Mimico Library	\n\n					\n		\n		March 26 @ 6:00 pm - 7:30 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		Interacthon at Mimico Library\n	\n\n\n										\n\n	\n					\n				Adults	\n\n				\n\n				\n	Come join our Interacthon! Talk\, Connect\, Practice English A marathon of interactive recreational\, social and informational activities for newcomers and community members! What's in it for you? Try new activities […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Fri		\n		\n			27		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		The Psychology of Love	\n\n					\n		\n		March 27 @ 3:00 pm - 5:00 pm	\n	\n					\n	\n		Parkdale Library	\n	\n		1303 Queen Street West\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n									\n\n				\n	What is happening in our brain when we fall in love? Come learn the science behind it all! For more information\, please get in touch with Daniella at DDjaigbe@culturelink.ca or […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Fri		\n		\n			27		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Finding Home Through Art	\n\n					\n		\n		March 27 @ 4:00 pm - 5:00 pm	\n	\n					\n	\n		CultureLink	\n	\n		2340 Dundas St W\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n					\n\n	\n					\n				Adults	\n\n				\n\n				\n	Join us for a relaxing afternoon of collage-making to reflect on your journey to Canada. Refreshments will be provided FREE TTC tickets for eligible participants For more information\, contact Charlotte […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Tue		\n		\n			31		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Youth Connect Hub	\n\n					\n		\n		March 31 @ 3:30 pm - 5:30 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		Youth Connect Hub\n	\n\n\n					\n	\n		CultureLink Children & Youth Centre	\n	\n		3535 Dundas Street West\, Toronto\, Ontario\, Canada	\n	\n									\n\n				\n	A safe and welcoming space for youth to connect\, relax\, and have fun. Enjoy group games\, creative activities\, food sessions\, and conversations that support emotional well-being and confidence. For Newcomer […] \n\n				\n			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n							\n				\n	\n		\n			April 2026		\n	\n\n\n				\n\n	\n	\n		\n			Tue		\n		\n			14		\n	\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n	\n\n\n			\n\n				\n					\n	\n		Youth Connect Hub	\n\n					\n		\n		April 14 @ 3:30 pm - 5:30 pm	\n	\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n	\n\n		Youth 